Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Reserve 1 tsp @soy sauce{2%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and place in a #zip-close bag{}; 
add @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and remaining 
soy sauce; seal to close. Shake until salmon is evenly coated. Set aside to 
marinate for ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of 
@salt{} in a #small pot{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low 
simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered until ready 
to serve.

While rice cooks, trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise. Place under a 
#plate{}; press down until cucumber halves break open. Cut crosswise into 
1-inch pieces. Peel and grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1/2 tsp.

To #bowl{} with reserved soy sauce, add @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and as much 
@horseradish paste{1%teaspoon} as you like; stir to combine.

In a second small, #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine cucumber, 1 TBSP 
@rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 1 tsp water, 1/2 tsp @sugar{1%teaspoon}, a big 
pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to 
pickle, tossing occasionally.

Line a #baking sheet{} with #foil{} and lightly oil with @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}.

Once salmon has marinated 10 minutes, place salmon on prepared sheet and brush 
with any excess marinade.

Roast on top rack until salmon is almost cooked through, ~{8%minutes}. Remove 
sheet from oven and brush salmon with half the @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}. 
Return to oven; roast until glaze is tacky and salmon is cooked through, 
~{2-4%minutes} more.

While salmon roasts, in a medium bowl, combine @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}, 
ginger, and 1/2 tsp vinegar. Stir in @edamame{4%ounce} and @shredded carrots{4%ounce} 
until coated.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in 1/2 tsp sugar and remaining vinegar to taste. 
Season with salt to taste.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with salmon, edamame salad, and pickled cucumber 
in separate sections. Sprinkle bowls with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and 
drizzle with spicy soy mayo. Serve.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.